Reviewed outside records as discussed in HPI.
#1 Young-onset rectal cancer
Discussed the development, staging, and treatment of rectal cancer with Mrs. Messersmith, as well as Lynch syndrome.  Given her young age of onset, she is agreeable to proceed with immunohistochemistry staining.  We will have her outside CT and chest x-ray sent to Radiology for interpretation, and will proceed with endoscopic ultrasound for staging purposes, after which she will meet with Colon and Rectal Surgery for consideration of surgical resection.  We discussed the role for neoadjuvant chemoradiation if T3 or N1 disease is identified.  It does not appear that a colonoscopy needs to be repeated.  I will follow-up with the patient throughout her examinations.
#2 Esophageal thickening on CT
An EGD will be requested at the time of her EUS.
Discussed with Dr. Kim Valenzuela.  Note to follow.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

